    <sec id="SEC2-2">
      <title>Hierarchical Bayesian modeling of diploid chromatin contact maps and 3D structures</title>
      <p>To model diploid Hi-C data, we propose a hierarchical Bayesian modeling framework for imputing the allele-specific chromatin contacts and reconstructing the allelic 3D structures. Specifically, we model the generation of allele-specific contacts with either a Poisson-multinomial process (the ASHIC-PM model) or a zero-inflated Poisson-multinomial process (the ASHIC-ZIPM model) for the inference of diploid contact matrices and 3D structures. The ASHIC-ZIPM model is a zero-inflated version of ASHIC-PM and it explicitly accounts for the excessive zeros observed in Hi-C contact matrices.</p>
      <p>Here, we describe ASHIC-ZIPM, the zero-inflated version of our hierarchical Bayesian model and the corresponding EM algorithm for model fitting. The details for the ASHIC-PM model are available in Supplementary Methods.</p>
